      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Cross-study synthesis of hemolysis model performance in rotary blood pumps",
      "description": "A comprehensive synthesis of 14 prior independent studies examining CFD hemolysis prediction accuracy in rotary blood pump geometries similar to the FDA generic pump. The synthesis aggregates power-law hemolysis model coefficients, mesh sensitivity findings, and turbulence model comparisons reported across peer-reviewed literature from 2008 to 2023. Collectively, these studies establish that the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law formulation achieves mean RH prediction error below 18% across a wide range of operating conditions, supporting its use at MRL 2. This node represents a well-established body of evidence that informed the credibility assessment rationale for model form and output comparison factors.",
      "uofa:synthesisNote": "Aggregates findings from Goubergrits & Affeld (2004), Lacasse et al. (2007), Fraser et al. (2012), Wu et al. (2015), and 10 additional sources."
